    <string name="hermes_permissions_card_title">Permissions checklist</string>
    <string name="hermes_permissions_card_body">If RUN_COMMAND stays “No” after the request, open Termux app info → Permissions → enable “Run commands” for LocalAgent. Allow notifications so long installs can post completion from Termux.</string>
    <string name="hermes_post_notif_granted">Notifications allowed</string>
    <string name="hermes_post_notif_denied">Notifications denied — enable in system settings for install feedback</string>
    <string name="hermes_bridge_listen_warning">Bridge and LLM HTTP listen on all interfaces so Termux (different Android UID) can reach this device on LAN IPv4. The bridge requires an AUTH line with LOCALAGENT_BRIDGE_TOKEN before any JSON. Avoid untrusted Wi‑Fi.</string>
    <string name="hermes_bridge_auth_title">Bridge wire protocol</string>
    <string name="hermes_bridge_auth_body">Right after TCP connect, send one line: the word AUTH, a space, then the hex LOCALAGENT_BRIDGE_TOKEN from copied bridge vars or ~/.hermes/.env. Leading blank lines are skipped. Then send newline-delimited JSON BridgeEvent lines as before.</string>
